author: itv.com
title: Eurotunnel service suspended following night of delays
text:
The Eurotunnel service at Folkestone has been suspended because of an earlier technical fault in the Tunnel.
For passengers, at the moment, there is a waiting time of approximately 60 minutes on the terminal.
For the latest information on the disruption, visit their website here.
Our passenger service is temporarily suspended due to an incident on the terminal which is in the process of being resolved. This information will be updated as soon as the service resumes. We sincerely apologise for the inconvenience this will cause to your journey.
